node.title: White House press secretary Jen Psaki tests positive for COVID-19
node.description: Psaki said she had two "socially-distanced" meetings with President Biden on Monday and said he is not considered a close contact.
node.content: ["White House press secretary Jen Psaki has tested positive for COVID-19, she announced Tuesday. Psaki said in a statement she had two \"socially-distanced\" meetings with President Biden on Monday and said he is not considered a close contact as defined by the CDC.", "Psaki said a PCR test she took Tuesday morning came back positive. She said she had taken the test as part of preparation for Mr. Biden's upcoming trip to Europe, which she will no longer be joining.", "Mr. Biden tested negative Tuesday through a PCR test, she said.", "Psaki, who is vaccinated, said she is only experiencing \"mild symptoms\" and will work from home until she is permitted to return in person under CDC guidelines.", "The positive test comes approximately five months after Psaki\u00a0last tested positive\u00a0for the virus.\u00a0", "This is a developing story. It will be updated. \u00a0", "Victoria Albert is a News Editor at CBS News. Reach her at victoria.albert@viacomcbs.com"]
